Civic Hack Saturday is a hands on meetup for â€œhackers" interested in contributing to civic apps. Developers, designers, writers, data analysis, policy wonks and people of all skill levels are encouraged to attend.Â


The event runs from 9am to 2pm, so feel free to drop in anytime between then. We'd like Civic Hack Saturday's to be an open space to come work on your civic projects. There won't be announcements or a presentation. Just come hack.


Please bring a laptop and be prepared to hack. If you have any project ideas, or are looking for a civic project to work on, see github.com/open-austin/project-ideas/issues.


If you have any questions, contact Luqmaan at hack@open-austin.org or ask us on theÂ Open Austin Slack Chat.

results.description:
Topic: Designing for 100% of America

Guest: Ben Guhin,Â UX Design Fellow at Consumer Financial Protection Bureau

Summary: Ben's presentation will touch on designing government services with ALL citizens in mind. This will cover accessibility, usability testing, and cross-channel services.

The program starts about 7pm.

--------------------

Open Austin hosts a monthly meet-up, to discuss local open government and civic technology issues. Our meet-ups are free and open to the public. Â The meetup location is easily accessed by public transportation and has plentiful parking.

For more information, visit our website: http://www.open-austin.org
